article.description: VMI beats High Point in overtime 82-80
article.headline: VMI beats High Point in overtime 82-80
article.linkText: VMI beats High Point in overtime 82-80
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. -- Rodney Glasgow followed his own miss with a left-handed putback with .6 seconds left in overtime and VMI pulled out an 82-80 victory over High Point on Wednesday night. John Brown made two free throws for High Point (6-12, 2/3 Big South) with 1:38 left in overtime to take an 80-78 lead and got the ball back after a turnover. But the Keydets' D.J. Covington intercepted a pass and, after teammate QJ Peterson missed a 3-pointer, slammed home the rebound with 47 seconds left. VMI (10-8, 3-2) got the ball back on a travel, setting up Glasgow's winning shot. Covington's two free throws with 9 seconds left in regulation sent the game into overtime at 75-all. Peterson led VMI with 25 points. Glasgow scored 18, Jordan Weethee 11 and Covington 10. Brown led the Panthers with 28 points with Adam Weary adding 17, Jorge Perez-Laham 16 and Devante Wallace 11.
